<div class="body">

<header>

<h1 data-aid="146039586" id="title1">You Can Gather Israel!</h1>
<div class="byline">
<p class="author-name" data-aid="146039594" id="author1">By Ahmad&nbsp;S. Corbitt</p>
<p class="author-role" data-aid="146039603" id="author2">First Counselor in the Young Men General Presidency</p>
</div>
<p class="kicker" data-aid="146039610" id="kicker1">I am absolutely sure you youth can do this because of something about your identity and an enormous power within you.</p>
</header>
<div class="body-block">
<p data-aid="146039618" id="p1">Almost three years ago, President Russell&nbsp;M. Nelson invited all youth of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints &#201C;to enlist in the Lord&#2019;s youth battalion to help gather Israel&#201D; on both sides of the veil. He said, &#201C;That gathering is the most important thing taking place on earth today.&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note1">1</a><span class="footnote">[Russell&nbsp;M. Nelson, &#201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/broadcasts/worldwide-devotional-for-young-adults/2018/06/hope-of-israel?lang=eng">Hope of Israel</a>&#201D; (worldwide youth devotional, June&nbsp;3, 2018), HopeofIsrael.ChurchofJesusChrist.org.]</span></sup> I am absolutely sure you youth can do this&#2014;and do it very well&#2014;because of (1) something about your identity and (2) an enormous power within you.</p>

<p data-aid="146039625" id="p2">Forty-one years ago, two missionaries from our Church felt led to a house in New Jersey, in the United States. In time, miraculously, both parents and all 10 children were baptized. In the prophet&#2019;s words, they &#201C;let God prevail&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note2">2</a><span class="footnote">[See Russell&nbsp;M. Nelson, &#201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/general-conference/2020/10/46nelson?lang=eng">Let God Prevail</a>,&#201D; <cite>Ensign</cite> or <cite>Liahona</cite>, Nov. 2020, 92&#2013;95.]</span></sup> in their lives. I should say &#201C;our lives.&#201D; I was the third child. I was 17 years old when I decided to make a permanent covenant to follow Jesus Christ. But guess what else I decided? I would not serve a full-time mission. That was too much. And this could not be expected of me, right? I was a brand-new Church member. I had no money. Besides, although I had just graduated from the toughest high school in nearby West Philadelphia and faced down some dangerous challenges, I was secretly terrified of leaving home for two whole years.</p>

<section>
<header>
<h2 data-aid="146039633" id="title2">Your True Identity</h2>
</header>
<p data-aid="146039641" id="p3">But I had just learned that I and all of humanity had lived with our Heavenly Father as His spirit sons and daughters before our birth. Others needed to know, as I knew, that He longed for all His children to enjoy eternal life with Him. So, before anyone was on earth, He presented all with His perfect plan of salvation and happiness, with Jesus Christ as our Savior. Tragically, Satan opposed God&#2019;s plan.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note3">3</a><span class="footnote">[See Gospel Topics, &#201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/manual/gospel-topics/plan-of-salvation?lang=eng">Plan of Salvation</a>,&#201D; topics.ChurchofJesusChrist.org; see also Henry&nbsp;B. Eyring, &#201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/general-conference/2019/04/34eyring?lang=eng">The Power of Sustaining Faith</a>,&#201D; <cite>Ensign</cite> or <cite>Liahona</cite>, May 2019, 58.]</span></sup> According to the book of Revelation, &#201C;there was war in heaven&#201D;!<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note4">4</a><span class="footnote">[See <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/nt/rev/12.7-8?lang=eng#p7">Revelation 12:7&#2013;8</a>.]</span></sup> Satan cunningly deceived a third part of Heavenly Father&#2019;s spirit children into letting him prevail instead of God.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note5">5</a><span class="footnote">[See <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/29.36-37?lang=eng#p36">Doctrine and Covenants 29:36&#2013;37</a>.]</span></sup> But not you! The Apostle John saw that you overcame Satan &#201C;by the word of [your] testimony.&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note6">6</a><span class="footnote">[<a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/nt/rev/12.11?lang=eng#p11">Revelation 12:11</a>.]</span></sup></p>
<p data-aid="146039651" id="p13">Knowing my true identity, helped by my patriarchal blessing, gave me the courage and faith to accept President Spencer&nbsp;W. Kimball&#2019;s invitation to gather Israel.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note7">7</a><span class="footnote">[See Spencer&nbsp;W. Kimball, &#201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/ensign/1977/10/it-becometh-every-man?lang=eng">It Becometh Every Man</a>,&#201D; <cite>Ensign</cite>, Oct. 1977, 2&#2013;7.]</span></sup> It will be the same for you, dear friends. Knowing you overcame Satan by the word of your testimony before will help you love, share, and invite<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note8">8</a><span class="footnote">[&#201C;<a href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/share">Sharing the Gospel</a>,&#201D; ChurchofJesusChrist.org/share.]</span></sup> now and always&#2014;to invite others to come and see, come and help, and come and belong, as that same war for the souls of God&#2019;s children rages on.</p>

</section>
<section>
<header>
<h2 data-aid="146039660" id="title3">The Powerful Faith within You</h2>
</header>
<p data-aid="146039669" id="p4">What about the enormous power within you? Think of this: you shouted for joy<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note9">9</a><span class="footnote">[See <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/ot/job/38.4-7?lang=eng#p4">Job 38:4&#2013;7</a>.]</span></sup> to come to a fallen world where all would face physical and spiritual death. We would never be able to overcome either on our own. We would suffer from not only our own sins but others&#2019; sins too. Humanity would experience virtually every imaginable type of brokenness and disappointment<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note10">10</a><span class="footnote">[See Gospel Topics, &#201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/manual/gospel-topics/plan-of-salvation?lang=eng">Plan of Salvation</a>&#201D;; see also &#201C;Be Still, My Soul,&#201D; <cite>Hymns</cite>, no.&nbsp;124, verse&nbsp;3.]</span></sup>&#2014;all with a veil of forgetfulness over our minds and the world&#2019;s worst enemy continuing to target and tempt us. All hope for returning resurrected and clean to God&#2019;s holy presence rested entirely upon one Being keeping His promise.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note11">11</a><span class="footnote">[See Gospel Topics, &#201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/manual/gospel-topics/plan-of-salvation?lang=eng">Plan of Salvation</a>&#201D;; see also Dallin&nbsp;H. Oaks, &#201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/general-conference/2020/04/51oaks?lang=eng">The Great Plan</a>,&#201D; <cite>Ensign</cite> or <cite>Liahona</cite>, May 2020, 93&#2013;94, 96.]</span></sup></p>
<p data-aid="146039678" id="p14">What empowered you to go forward? President Henry&nbsp;B. Eyring taught, &#201C;It took faith in Jesus Christ to sustain the plan of happiness and Jesus Christ&#2019;s place in it when you knew so little of the challenges that you would face in mortality.&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note12">12</a><span class="footnote">[Henry&nbsp;B. Eyring, &#201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/general-conference/2019/04/34eyring?lang=eng">The Power of Sustaining Faith</a>,&#201D; 58.]</span></sup> When Jesus Christ promised He would come into mortality and give His life to gather<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note13">13</a><span class="footnote">[See <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/27.14?lang=eng#p14">3&nbsp;Nephi 27:14</a>.]</span></sup> and save us, you did not simply believe Him. You &#201C;noble spirits&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note14">14</a><span class="footnote">[Russell&nbsp;M. Nelson, &#201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/broadcasts/worldwide-devotional-for-young-adults/2018/06/hope-of-israel?lang=eng">Hope of Israel</a>,&#201D; HopeofIsrael.ChurchofJesusChrist.org; see also <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/138.55-56?lang=eng#p55">Doctrine and Covenants 138:55&#2013;56</a>.]</span></sup> had such &#201C;exceedingly great faith&#201D; that you saw His promise as sure.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note15">15</a><span class="footnote">[See <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/13.2-4?lang=eng#p2">Alma 13:2&#2013;4</a>; see also <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/nt/rev/12.11?lang=eng#p11">Revelation 12:11</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/pgp/a-of-f/1.5?lang=eng#p5">Articles of Faith 1:5</a>. The Book of Mormon makes clear that those with &#201C;exceedingly great faith&#201D; see God&#2019;s promises as already fulfilled. See <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/5.5?lang=eng#p5">1&nbsp;Nephi 5:5</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/3.11-13?lang=eng#p11">Mosiah 3:11&#2013;13</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.1-3?lang=eng#p1">4:1&#2013;3</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/27.28?lang=eng#p28">Alma 27:28</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/28.12?lang=eng#p12">28:12</a> (&#201C;they <em>are</em> raised&#201D; in 77&#2013;76 BC; emphasis added); see also <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/ot/ex/3.13?lang=eng#p13">Exodus 3:13</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/ot/isa/53?lang=eng">Isaiah 53</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/130.7?lang=eng#p7">Doctrine and Covenants 130:7</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/pgp/moses/7.47?lang=eng#p47">Moses 7:47</a>.]</span></sup> He could not lie, so you saw Him as if He had already shed His blood for you, long before He was born.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note16">16</a><span class="footnote">[See <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/31.15?lang=eng#p15">2&nbsp;Nephi 31:15</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/ether/3.6-9,11-13?lang=eng#p6">Ether 3:6&#2013;9, 11&#2013;13</a>. Faith to see Christ&#2019;s promise of salvation as already fulfilled necessarily requires knowing Christ cannot lie. Such faith is a defining characteristic of the premortal faithful, particularly our youth. &#201C;Our Heavenly Father has reserved many of His most noble spirits&#2014;perhaps, I might say, His finest team&#2014;for this final phase. Those noble spirits&#2014;those finest players, those heroes&#2014;are <em>you</em>!&#201D; (Russell&nbsp;M. Nelson, &#201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/broadcasts/worldwide-devotional-for-young-adults/2018/06/hope-of-israel?lang=eng">Hope of Israel</a>,&#201D; HopeofIsrael.ChurchofJesusChrist.org). See also <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/nt/john/1.1?lang=eng#p1">John 1:1</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/nt/john/14.6,17?lang=eng#p6">14:6, 17</a>.]</span></sup></p>
<p data-aid="146039685" id="p15">In John&#2019;s symbolic words, you &#201C;overcame [Satan] by the blood of the Lamb.&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note17">17</a><span class="footnote">[<a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/nt/rev/12.11?lang=eng#p11">Revelation 12:11</a>; see also <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/ether/3.6-9?lang=eng#p6">Ether 3:6&#2013;9</a>.]</span></sup> President Dallin&nbsp;H. Oaks taught that in that world &#201C;[you] saw the end from the beginning.&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note18">18</a><span class="footnote">[Dallin&nbsp;H. Oaks, &#201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/general-conference/2020/04/51oaks?lang=eng">The Great Plan</a>,&#201D; 93.]</span></sup></p>
<p data-aid="146039690" id="p5">Suppose one day before you leave for school, one of your parents makes a true promise that you can have your favorite food when you return home! You are excited! While in school you imagine eating that food, and you can already taste it. Naturally, you share your good news with others. Looking forward to going home makes you so happy that the tests and challenges of school seem light. Nothing can take away your joy or make you doubt because of how sure the promise is! Similarly, before you noble spirits were born, you learned to see Christ&#2019;s promises in this sure way, and you tasted of His salvation.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note19">19</a><span class="footnote">[See <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/36.24-26?lang=eng#p24">Alma 36:24&#2013;26</a>; see also <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/ot/ps/34.8?lang=eng#p8">Psalm 34:8</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/jacob/3.2?lang=eng#p2">Jacob 3:2</a>; <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.11?lang=eng#p11">Mosiah 4:11</a>.]</span></sup> Your great faith is like muscles that get stronger and bigger the more you exercise them, but they are already inside you.</p>
<p data-aid="146039697" id="p6">How can you awaken your giant faith in Christ and use it to gather Israel now and triumph over Satan again? By relearning to look forward and see with that same certainty the Lord&#2019;s promise to gather and save today. He mainly uses the Book of Mormon and His prophets to teach us how. Long before Christ, the Nephite &#201C;prophets, and&nbsp;&#2026; priests, and&nbsp;&#2026; teachers&nbsp;&#2026; [persuaded the people] to look forward unto the Messiah, and believe in him to come as though he already was.&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note20">20</a><span class="footnote">[<a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/jarom/1.11?lang=eng#p11">Jarom 1:11</a>.]</span></sup> The prophet Abinadi taught, &#201C;And now if Christ had not come into the world, speaking of things to come as though they had already come, there could have been no redemption.&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note21">21</a><span class="footnote">[<a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/16.6?lang=eng#p6">Mosiah 16:6</a>.]</span></sup> Like Alma, Abinadi &#201C;look[ed] forward with an eye of faith&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note22">22</a><span class="footnote">[<a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/5.15?lang=eng#p15">Alma 5:15</a>.]</span></sup> and saw God&#2019;s sure promise of salvation as already fulfilled. They &#201C;overcame [Satan] by the blood of the Lamb, and&nbsp;&#2026; the word of their testimony&#201D; long before Christ was born, just as you did. And the Lord gave them power to invite and gather Israel. He will do the same for you as you look forward in faith, see Israel gathered&#2014;globally and in your own &#201C;circles&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note23">23</a><span class="footnote">[See &#201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/new-era/2020/10/gospel-living-circles?lang=eng">Gospel Living: Circles</a>,&#201D; <cite>New Era</cite>, Oct. 2020, 15.]</span></sup>&#2014;and invite all!</p>
<p data-aid="146039704" id="p16">Hundreds of missionaries built upon their powerful premortal faith in Christ by envisioning those they contacted or taught dressed in baptismal and temple clothing. In a talk titled &#201C;Begin with the End in Mind,&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note24">24</a><span class="footnote">[See Russell&nbsp;M. Nelson, &#201C;Begin with the End in Mind&#201D; (address given at the seminar for new mission presidents, June&nbsp;22, 2014).]</span></sup> President Nelson shared a personal example of doing this and instructed mission leaders to teach our missionaries to do the same. Knowing they exercised this great faith in Jesus Christ in the premortal world immensely helped our dear missionaries &#201C;hear Him&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note25">25</a><span class="footnote">[See Russell&nbsp;M. Nelson, &#201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/general-conference/2020/04/45nelson?lang=eng">Hear Him</a>,&#201D; <cite>Ensign</cite> or <cite>Liahona</cite>, May 2020, 88&#2013;92.]</span></sup> and activate their enormous faith to gather Israel as the Lord promised.</p>
<p data-aid="146039711" id="p7">Of course, imagining lies harms faith.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note26">26</a><span class="footnote">[For example, Alma spoke to his people about looking forward with an eye of faith to when they would stand before God but warned they could not imagine doing so with confidence and peace unless they had repented of their sins (see <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/5.15-17?lang=eng#p15">Alma 5:15&#2013;17</a>).]</span></sup> My friends, intentionally envisioning or viewing things that conflict with who you really are, especially pornography, will weaken your faith in Christ and, without repentance, could destroy it. Please use your imaginations to increase faith in Christ, not ruin it.</p>
</section>
<section>
<header>
<h2 data-aid="146039718" id="title4">The Children and Youth Program</h2>
</header>
<p data-aid="146039726" id="p8">The Children and Youth program is a prophetic tool to help you youth power up your great faith. President Oaks taught, &#201C;This program is designed to help you become more like our Savior in four areas: spiritual, social, physical, and intellectual.&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note27">27</a><span class="footnote">[<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/video/face-to-face-events/2020-02-1000-face-to-face-with-president-and-sister-oaks-1080p-eng?lang=eng">Face to Face with President and Sister Oaks</a> (worldwide youth and children&#2019;s broadcast, Feb.&nbsp;23, 2020), facetoface.ChurchofJesusChrist.org.]</span></sup> As you youth lead&#2014;<em>lead</em>&#2014;in living the gospel, caring for others, inviting all to receive the gospel, uniting families for eternity, and organizing fun activities,<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note28">28</a><span class="footnote">[See <cite><a class="cross-ref" href="/study/manual/general-handbook/title-page?lang=eng">General Handbook: Serving in The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints</a></cite>, 1.2; 10.2.1.3; 11.2.1.3, ChurchofJesusChrist.org.]</span></sup> the great faith in Christ you had in the premortal life will resurface and empower you to do His work in this life!</p>
<p data-aid="146039734" id="p17">Also, personal goals, &#201C;especially short-term goals,&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note29">29</a><span class="footnote">[<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/video/face-to-face-events/2020-02-1000-face-to-face-with-president-and-sister-oaks-1080p-eng?lang=eng">Face to Face with President and Sister Oaks</a>, facetoface.ChurchofJesusChrist.org.]</span></sup> help you reignite your powerful faith. When you set a good goal, you are looking forward, as you did before, and seeing what your Heavenly Father wants you or another to become.<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note30">30</a><span class="footnote">[See <cite><a class="cross-ref" href="/study/manual/preach-my-gospel-a-guide-to-missionary-service/how-do-i-use-time-wisely?lang=eng">Preach My Gospel: A Guide to Missionary Service</a></cite> (2018), 156, ChurchofJesusChrist.org; see also <a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/alma/5.15-17?lang=eng#p15">Alma 5:15&#2013;17</a>.]</span></sup> Then you plan and work hard to achieve it. Elder Quentin&nbsp;L. Cook taught, &#201C;Never underestimate the importance of planning, setting goals&nbsp;&#2026;&nbsp;, and [inviting others]&#2014;all with an eye of faith.&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note31">31</a><span class="footnote">[Quentin&nbsp;L. Cook, &#201C;Purpose and Planning&#201D; (address given at the seminar for new mission presidents, June 25, 2019).]</span></sup></p>
<p data-aid="146039742" id="p18">The choice is yours! The Lord said of you, &#201C;The power [to choose] is in them.&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note32">32</a><span class="footnote">[<a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/58.28?lang=eng#p28">Doctrine and Covenants 58:28</a>.]</span></sup> Elder Neil&nbsp;L. Andersen explained, &#201C;Your faith will grow not by chance, but by choice.&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note33">33</a><span class="footnote">[Neil&nbsp;L. Andersen, &#201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/general-conference/2015/10/faith-is-not-by-chance-but-by-choice?lang=eng">Faith Is Not by Chance, but by Choice</a>,&#201D; <cite>Ensign</cite> or <cite>Liahona</cite>, Nov. 2015, 66.]</span></sup> He also said, &#201C;[Any] honest questions [you may have]&nbsp;&#2026; will be settled with patience and an eye of faith.&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note34">34</a><span class="footnote">[Neil&nbsp;L. Andersen, &#201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/general-conference/2019/04/25andersen?lang=eng">The Eye of Faith</a>,&#201D; <cite>Ensign</cite> or <cite>Liahona</cite>, May 2019, 36.]</span></sup></p>
<p data-aid="146039750" id="p9">I testify that (1) your true identity and (2) the enormous power of faith in Christ within you will enable you to &#201C;help prepare the world for the Savior&#2019;s return by inviting all to come unto Christ and receive the blessings of His Atonement.&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note35">35</a><span class="footnote">[&#201C;<a class="cross-ref" href="/study/manual/aaronic-priesthood-quorum-theme/aaronic-priesthood-quorum-theme?lang=eng">Aaronic Priesthood Quorum Theme</a>,&#201D; ChurchofJesusChrist.org.]</span></sup> May we all share the joy of the Book of Mormon&#2019;s sure promise:</p>
<p data-aid="146039758" id="p10">&#201C;The righteous that hearken unto the&nbsp;&#2026; prophets, and&nbsp;&#2026; look forward unto Christ with steadfastness&nbsp;&#2026; notwithstanding all persecution&nbsp;&#2026; shall not perish.</p>
<p data-aid="146039765" id="p11">&#201C;But [Christ]&nbsp;&#2026; shall heal them, and they shall have peace with him.&#201D;<sup class="noteMarker"><a href="#note36">36</a><span class="footnote">[<a class="scripture-ref" href="/study/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/26.8-9?lang=eng#p8">2&nbsp;Nephi 26:8&#2013;9</a>.]</span></sup></p>
<p data-aid="146039772" id="p12">In the name of Jesus Christ, amen.</p>
</section>
</div>
